# Documentation maintenance

Keep `.cursor/rules/` operational and short. Do not paste long architecture or troubleshooting prose into always-loaded rules.

Structure:

- root `README.md` — public-facing setup and features;
- `.cursor/rules/` — agent instructions;
- root `TODO.md` — unresolved work (local-only);
- `docs/architecture.md`, `docs/project-notes.md`, `docs/testing.md`, `docs/troubleshooting.md` — durable reference (local-only);
- `docs/index.html` — public stats dashboard generated by the workflow.

When a change teaches durable architecture, validation, or operating knowledge, update the matching doc under `docs/` rather than expanding rules.
